The paper discusses domain-specific languages (DSLs) for spatial computing, which involves the coordination of multiple computing devices in a physical space. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including multi-agent systems (cs.MA), distributed computing (cs.DC), software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), and control systems (cs.SY). However, since the paper focuses on DSLs and their application to spatial computing, we believe that cs.MA is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.DC and cs.SE. The other two sub-categories are less likely but still relevant to the paper's content.
